Git Command You should now.

1. git --version            (to get the version of git)
2. git cd                   (to change the directory)
3. git ls                   (to list all files and directories in this directory)
4. git status               (to check the file that tracked or not before we add to tracked list)
5. git add FILE_NAME        (to add file or directory to tracked list)
6. git commit -m "Message or Description to the file"(to commit the new file to repository in github)
7. git add -A               (to add all file or directory to tracked list)
8  Esc -> wq                (to exit the commit prompt when you didn't give the message -m to it)
